<br>
In any case, the kunark armor IS dropped directlty. One of the velious armors IS dropped directly. The other three are dropped indirectly...but when you get that drop (the armor piece), the rest of the quest is cake -- almost the same as if you'd gotten the armor directly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uvecsusbst.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VecsusBST</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Lord</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/17/02 6:58:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beastlord Only Equiptment</span><hr size=1> i doubt the monk community is worried about losing all their precious loot to beastlords.  A large portion of the lvl 55+ BST community is comprised of alts.  most guilds will give an item to a Main monk before they will give it to an alt BST.  That only makes sense.  Those of us that are lvl 55+ and play a BST as our primary (my only character over level 10) are often hoping few monk show up for a raid or for items to drop that are not upgrades for the monks that do attend.<br>
<br>
and my view on quest armor stands.  since all classes get quest armor it levels the playing field back to zero.  now add up the number of items in a zone like ToV that are usable in each class and total it up.   in fact, after lunch i will do just that. <p>Vecsus Strangiato <br>
